					<div class="leftnote"><span class="xar-sub">Posted Feb 20, 2005 at 12:15:41 PM</span></div>
										<div style="float: left;"><strong class="xar-sub">Subject: rude comments in the work place.
</strong></div>
					<div style="clear: both;"></div>
				</div>
				<div>
															<p>such as &quot;I can tell just by looking at you that you arn't that smart and didn't do to well in high school&quot;. It's statements like these that I've had to put up with from people in past jobs. What would posses someone to say something that cruel? </p>
<p>I'm not an aggressive person, I'm shy and keep to myself mostly. I do my job and go home that's it. But that's not enough for most people, they see that I'm an easy target, and feel that it's their duty say maliciouse things.</p>
<p>I hate having a low average iq!</p>
									</div>
							</td>
